The day I knew would come… but never felt ready for.

Leaving a piece of my heart at home as I step back into the world outside.
The quiet mornings, the snuggles, her tiny hands holding on… all of it plays on a loop in my mind.

This isn’t just about going back to work.
It’s about letting go a little, while holding on with everything I have.

To every mama who’s cried in silence before walking out the door — I see you.
And to my little Rumi…
Mama’s doing this for you. Always for you. 💔🌸
